			<ns0:name>ncb...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/100032148147647801554/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Upcall channel death should be reported and used as an indicator the nexe is dead.  This is an interesting case because it would mean we could detect the nexe died without attempting to communicate with it.  Reporting the upcall channel's death is a little tricky because it will be detected off the main thread, and the notification then needs to be sent to the main thread.

I have a partial CL for this functionality, but I am stalled on sorting out the threading, communication, and object lifetime issues.

